N:Closely related to "Devil's Dream." Old‑Time, USA; Arkansas, Missouri. Standard tuning. AABB. The title appears in a list of traditional tunes played by Ozark Mountains fiddlers compiled by musicologist/folklorist Vance Randolph, published in 1954.  Source for notated version: Sam Eads (Dixon, Missouri) [Christeson]. R.P. Christeson (Old Time Fiddler's Repertory, vol. 2), 1984; pg. 3. Ford (Traditional Music in America), 1940; pg. 79.

